post_text: Our first round of PPE Face Shields are headed to local first responders!!! Thank you for all you do! Thank you to the local donors, the WG MakerDen and the WG Stem Dept for making this happen! If you are interested in donating please contact Brian Shaw or Tyler Turner @ 419-568-9114 - brian.shaw@wgschools.org - tyler.turner@wgschools.org. Items that are needed: clear plastic 8 1/2 x 11 8mil + sheets, rubber bands, 1/8' elastic mask cord, or any monetary donations. Our next rounds will be going to anyone that needs them with a focus on local hospitals! If you are in need of shields, please let us know! #WGTigerProud #

post_text: The W-G Athletic Department will be selling old football, basketball and cheerleading uniforms and W-G memorabilia for anyone that may be interested. If you're interested in a particular size, color, or jersey number, feel free to contact AD Nathan Swaney at 419-568-1013 and at nathan.swaney@wgschools.org or Tim Buffenbarger at 419-568-1012. We will also be selling these items at upcoming boys and girls basketball games!

post_text: The indoor track and field team is selling pork loin dinner tickets. The dinner is on Friday, December 20th from 5-7. The tickets are $7 dollars and the meal includes a 10 oz. pork loin, baked potato, roll and side. You may eat in or carry out. This is a fundraiser to help offset the cost of entry fees into the meets. You may purchase tickets from an indoor track team member or call the board office at 419-568-9100 ext. 1
